title: Considerations when working with data from multiple third parties
Establishing the suitability of data prior to access and reuse
displayTitle: Establishing the suitability of data prior to access and reuse
body:
As a user of the third-party data, beyond obtaining permission to reuse the data, you will need to check the practical reusability of the data.

This is a complex phase that could take a significant amount of time. Before acquiring the data it may well be possible to ascertain some of the ethical risks relating to the data including:

title: Is data ethics only a consideration when handling personal data?
Is data ethics important, or is it critical?
Is data ethics only a consideration when handling personal data?
Data ethics across the data lifecycle?
Asking the right questions?
body: There are different considerations to be made across each stage of the data lifecycle. Regardless of the stage you are working at, when doing an ethical evaluation it is always important to ask the opposite question in order to provide balance. Such questions can also provide greater clarity on the ethical consequences. It is also important to ask the opposite questions of the ones usually posed.
